    '[[*pagetitle]]' => 'Expedia Releases Insiders List of Top Hotels',
    '[[*frontPageImage]]' => '<img src="/assets/research assets/hospitality/images/130809_One-Only-Palmilla-Los-Cabos.png" alt="" />',
    '[[*category]]' => 'Hospitality',
    '[[*createdby:userinfo=`fullname`]]' => 'Timothy Voice',
    '[[*createdon:strtotime:date=`%m/%d`]]' => '08/09',
    '[[*reportDownload]]' => '',
    '[[$researchPostBasic]]' => '<!--researchPost-->
<div class="two-thirds column omega" id="report_container">
<div><a href="index.php?id=76" id="blog_title"><h3>Expedia Releases Insiders List of Top Hotels</h3></a>
</div>
<div class="two-thirds column alpha"><img src="/assets/research assets/hospitality/images/130809_One-Only-Palmilla-Los-Cabos.png" alt="" /></div>
<br class="clear" />
<div id="frontpage_story_category"><h5>Hospitality</h5></div>
<div id="frontpage_story_meta">by Timothy Voice, on 08/09</div>
<div id="report_download"></div>



<div id="main_story"><p>This week Expedia, a user review site with more than 130,000 hotels in its databases, released their <a title="Expedia\'s Insider Select List" href="http://www.expedia.ca/p/hotel-deal/insiders-select.htm" target="_blank">Insiders’ Select list</a> of the world’s top hotels. The ranking is based on more than 500,000 guest reviews and expert input.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Here’s a quick look at the top 3.</p>
<p> </p>
<h4>One&amp;Only Palmilla Resort</h4>
<p> </p>
<p><img src="assets/research%20assets/hospitality/images/130809_One&amp;Only_Room.png" alt="One&amp;Only Room View" width="620" height="348" /></p>
<p> </p>
<p>(San Jose Del Cabo, Mexico)</p>
<p>From $488/night</p>
<p><em> </em></p>
<p><em>“The resort’s rooms (173 in total) have all the luxe touches you’d expect — lavish bathrooms, flat-screen televisions, Bose surround sound — plus such surprise extras as telescopes on every balcony for whale-watching by day and stargazing by night. Even the smallest rooms are essentially suites, but it’s the level of service that sets the resort apart. From welcome drinks and a butler (who will unpack your bags for you) to poolside foot massages and aromatherapy turndown service, you’ll feel pampered from arrival to departure.”</em></p>
<p>-<a title="Jetsetter" href="http://www.jetsetter.com/hotels/mexico/los-cabos/2981/one-only-palmilla" target="_blank">Jetsetter</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>A long-time celebrity haunt, The One&amp;Only may be the priciest resort in the top three but it is clear that people are willing to part with the extra cash for the superior service and added amenities such as garment pressing and a personal butler to help you settle into your room.</p>
<p> </p>
<h4>Arenas del Mar Beachfront &amp; Rainforest Resort</h4>
<p> </p>
<p><img src="assets/research%20assets/hospitality/images/130809_Arenas-del-Mar_Room.png" alt="Arenas View" width="620" height="348" /></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">(Quepos, Costa Rica)</span></p>
<p>From $270/night</p>
<p><em> </em></p>
<p><em>“Down-to-earth eco-chic comes standard at this 11-acre rain-forest-and-beach resort with a conscience. A go-to hideaway for adventure-seeking, luxury-loving travelers, Arenas del Mar harmoniously mixes creature comforts with authentic experience, without disturbing its pristine Pacific coast location. The setting is one of the resort’s greatest assets, and each of the 38 rooms and suites has a spectacular view of either the rain forest or one of two white sand beaches on the Pacific.”</em></p>
<p>-<a title="Jetsetter" href="http://www.jetsetter.com/hotels/costa-rica/manuel-antonio-national-park/800/arenas-del-mar-resort?nm=serplist&amp;cl=1&amp;ca=view-more" target="_blank">Jetsetter</a></p>
<p> <span style="line-height: 1.5em;"> </span></p>
<p>Whereas One&amp;Only excel at service, Arenas del Mar’s highlight is the location. They take full advantage of the crashing waves and rain forest atmosphere with expansive wrap-around terraces attached to each room. Arenas exposes you to your natural surroundings and then gently get out of the way, stepping in only to ensure comfort and relaxation. Bird watching, zip-lining, jungle tours and indigenous crafting are all popular activities offered by the hotel.</p>
<p> </p>
<h4>Marrol’s Boutique Hotel</h4>
<p> </p>
<p><img src="assets/research%20assets/hospitality/images/130809_Hotel-Marrols_Exterior.png" alt="Marrol\'s Exterior" width="620" height="348" /></p>
<p>(Bratislava, Slovakia)</p>
<p>From $180/night</p>
<p><em> </em></p>
<p><em>”This luxury boutique hotel, a member of the prestigious Small Luxury Hotels of the World, has only 54 guest rooms and suites. It has all the amenities you\'d expect from a 5-star hotel—a superb restaurant, a full spa, luxurious rooms—and an excellent location in the heart of Old Town\'s charming cobble-stoned streets. But that\'s not the biggest draw, according to Expedia users: it\'s the price.”</em></p>
<p>-<a title="Business Insider" href="http://www.businessinsider.com/worlds-best-hotel-according-to-expedia-users-2012-6" target="_blank">Business Insider</a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Marrol’s was Expedia’s number 1 pick in 2012, a spot it earned with its tremendous value. At $180/night including breakfast, there is plenty cash left over to enjoy the full spa and local attractions. The restaurant, like the hotel itself embraces the local culture; you wont find overplayed modern dining here, only refined old-world cuisine in a traditional setting. Value and cultural rootedness are what make Marrol’s stand out in this years top list.</p></div>



</div><!--end report_container-->
',
